Chapter 3: What Must Be Repaired?
Core Question
What weakened trust during the first container?
Understand
Repair is part of institution building.
A society that cannot repair cannot endure.
Do not move into the next phase carrying hidden confusion, resentment, unclear money, vague roles, broken privacy, or unfinished conflict.
Growth magnifies what is unresolved.
If the ledger was unclear, fix it before expanding.
If roles were invisible, define them before adding new projects.
If meetings drifted, strengthen the rhythm before inviting more people.
If privacy was violated, repair it before handling deeper needs.
Repair is not delay.
Repair is preparation.
Discuss
Where did trust weaken?
Was money clear?
Were roles clear?
Did anyone carry too much?
Was privacy protected?
Did conflict stay repairable?
What must be fixed before we grow?
