PART TWO: STRENGTHEN THE FOUNDATION

Chapter 4: Strengthen the Roles
Core Question
Are our roles strong enough for the next phase?
Understand
Roles protect people from burnout.
When roles are unclear, the most responsible people carry too much, and the least responsible people remain invisible.
The next container needs stronger role clarity than the first container.
The society should confirm:
Who facilitates?
 Who keeps records?
 Who handles treasury?
 Who checks treasury?
 Who coordinates care?
 Who manages the next project?
 Who reports?
 Who protects privacy?
 Who trains the next person?
Every role should have:
A person
 A backup
 A clear responsibility
 A reporting rhythm
 A replacement plan
Discuss
Which roles worked?
Which roles were unclear?
Who carried too much?
Who needs a backup?
Which new role is needed for the next container?
