Chapter 5: Strengthen the Rules
Core Question
What rules need to be revised now that we have experience?
Understand
Early rules are written before pressure.
Next rules are improved after experience.
The first 100 days probably revealed gaps.
Maybe aid eligibility was unclear.
Maybe privacy needed more detail.
Maybe dues needed flexibility.
Maybe decision-making was too slow.
Maybe role rotation was missing.
This is not failure.
It means the society is learning.
A rule should be strong enough to guide action and humble enough to be revised.
Discuss
Which rule was unclear?
Which rule protected us?
Which rule was missing?
What decision created confusion?
What must be changed before the next container begins?
