Chapter 6: Strengthen the Treasury
Core Question
Can our money system carry more responsibility?
Understand
Before the society grows, the money system must be tested.
Ask:
Was every contribution recorded?
Were reports shared on time?
Did members understand the balance?
Were aid decisions documented?
Was privacy protected?
Did two-person oversight work?
Did the reserve rule make sense?
A society should not raise more money until it can clearly account for the money it already handled.
More money does not fix weak treasury.
It exposes it.
Discuss
Was the ledger clean?
Were reports consistent?
Was the approval process clear?
Did anyone have too much private control?
Should dues stay the same or change?
What reserve goal should we set?
Build: Treasury Strengthening Worksheet
